<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Programmers Hierarchical Interactive Graphics System" class="currentChild" href="Programmers_Hierarchical_Interactive_Graphics_System">Programmers Hierarchical Interactive Graphics System</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In computer graphics, a set of standards—developed jointly by <a title="ANSI" href="http://printwiki.org/ANSI">ANSI</a> and <a title="ISO" href="ISO">ISO</a>—comprising a graphics system and language used for two-dimensional and three-dimensional images that acts as a device-independent <a title="Interface" href="Interface">interface</a> between an application and a graphic subsystem. PHIGS, however, is a comprehensive system that requires high-end workstations and host processors. An extension, <a title="PHIGS+" href="PHIGS+">PHIGS+</a>, adds data to three-dimensional models concerning lighting and shading. 
</p>
